# Day 11: Inheritance - The "IS-A" Relationship

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. Concept of Inheritance (Parent/Super Class vs Child/Sub Class).
2. The `extends` keyword.
3. `super` keyword to access parent class members.
4. Types of Inheritance (Single, Multilevel, Hierarchical).

**Learning Summary:**
Today I learned how to reuse code effectively using Inheritance. If a generic class (like `Animal`) already exists, I can create a specific class (like `Dog`) that inherits all properties of `Animal` without rewriting code. This establishes a parent-child relationship.

**Code Snippet:**
```java
// Parent Class
class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("This animal eats food.");
    }
}

// Child Class
class Dog extends Animal {
    void bark() {
        System.out.println("The dog barks.");
    }
}

public class Day11 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Dog myDog = new Dog();
        myDog.eat();  // Inherited method
        myDog.bark(); // Own method
    }
}
